org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions

Class TypeDefinitionBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.DefinitionBase
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.ScopedDefinitionBase
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.MemberedDefinition
          • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.TypeDefinitionBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMemberedDefinition, IScopedDefinition, ITypeDefinition, IDefinitionSet
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClassDefinitionBase, ClassTraitsDefinition, InterfaceDefinition

    public abstract class TypeDefinitionBase
extends MemberedDefinition
implements ITypeDefinition
    Instances of this class represent definitions of ActionScript types (i.e., classes and interfaces) in the symbol table.

    After a type definition is in the symbol table, it should always be accessed through the read-only ITypeDefinition, IClassDefinition, or IInterfaceDefinition interfaces.

      • isInstanceOf

        public boolean isInstanceOf(String qualifiedName,
                   ICompilerProject project)
        Description copied from interface: ITypeDefinition
        A variant of isInstanceOf which takes a fully-qualified type name rather than an ITypeDefinition.

        While not @deprecated, this method may not do what you want because the scope containing this type definition will be used to resolve the name that is specified rather than some other scope which may actually contain the name in source code.

        Specified by:
        isInstanceOf in interface ITypeDefinition
        Parameters:
        qualifiedName - A String, such as "flash.display.Sprite" , that specified a fully-qualified type name.
        project - The ICompilerProject within which references should be resolved
        Returns:
        A flag indicating whether an "is-a" relationship exists between the two types.

      • getNode

        public ITypeNode getNode()
        Description copied from interface: IDefinition
        Returns the IDefinitionNode from which this definition was created, if the definition came from the AST for a source file.

        This method may require the AST to be reloaded or regenerated and therefore may be slow.

        More specific definition interfaces such as IClassDefinition redeclare this method to return a more specific node interface such as IClassNode.

        Specified by:
        getNode in interface IDefinition
        Specified by:
        getNode in interface ITypeDefinition
